:INFO
Before You Start Wiring
This page describes connections involving 120V or 240V AC mains voltage. If \
you are not comfortable working with mains voltage, have a licensed electrician \
review your work before powering the circuit. Always build with the enclosure \
unplugged. Use appropriately rated wire (14 AWG minimum for 15-amp circuits \
in North America), proper insulated connectors, and a grounded metal or \
reinforced plastic enclosure.

:PATH
Power Supply Connections
The PID controller requires a 12V DC supply.
|
:INFO
Power Supply Connections
The PID controller requires a 12V DC supply. Mount a small switching power supply (5W or \
more) inside the enclosure. Connect the AC input of the power supply to the incoming AC \
line and neutral conductors via a terminal block. Connect the DC output

